Everyone in Inkopolis knows Maiku's story by heart. A story of too-large hope and a LOT of luck.  When he rode into Inkopolis by taxi since his mother was drunk (again), he had a smile. Finally a chance to show himself. To show how good of a singer he's been recently...and maybe to get some pocket change. He never smiled until that very day. One day, he found a man named Idunno. His hair was different than all the other Inklings...More pretty, somehow. He became good friends in a second with him, telling him his plan and always being told how insane of an idea it is. Even another inkling who came up, Clip, became friends with him. Unlike Idunno, Clip liked his insane ideas and always told him to keep on. So, he did. After another day of singing in Inkopolis Square with a boombox and gathering crowds larger than the Sermon on the Mount, he recognized two infamous inklings. Pearl and Marina. the Off the Hook band, and idols in Inkopolis. Marina seemed to stare a lot while Pearl hated seeing someone good at singing. They stayed their distance until.. A day after singing for pocket change, Marina came up to him with an offer. If he could win in a 1v2 Turf War against her and Pearl, she'd let him join their band. For reference, Maiku only played turf war with Idunno. Idunno was an excellent fighter and Maiku was an excellent turfer. When he heard this he immediately accepted. It was a shot, right? Like that one song he always sang.  *If you had, one shot, one opportunity to have everything you've ever wished for, would you take it? or let it slip away?* He was told off by Idunno that he could never win it, but he kept practicing no matter what. Idunno stopped telling him off eventually, and helped him practice. For a long while they practiced until they were machines at Turf War..and able to win at any cost. After the match, he won by pure hope. And finallly got to play in a concert on the big stage, with Off the Hook...And learned to play the guitar. Now Maiku is Off the Hook's lead guitarist, and smiles every day.  Subscribe to my channel and in a few years, you'll get notifications for tons of animated stories of my characters, done using MOCAP suits and custom models. All in the Pretend World. "Just think you can do it, that's all it takes, don't it?" -Maiku

This song puts me in a good mood. I used to love listening to this song when I was 7, and this song would always come on when my aunt drove me to Five Below to get Slime Lickers. Lol! It was a good vibe. Everytime I would go on a drive with her, I would ask her if we could go to Five Below to get Slime Lickers, since it was the trend then and everyone was making DIY ones and trying them on social media (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube etc.) and everyone was saying they were at Five Below so sometimes me and my aunt would go there to not only get Slime Lickers, but probably other cutesy nice decorative items or accessories. And when we would drive there, sometimes she would play this song or it would come on and overall not just the memory of driving to Five Below to get Slime Lickers with my aunt, but overall no matter when I listen to it or where I listen to it, it gives you good vibes. It's got that melody, that  tune, the beat the happiness. This song was very popular too! I also liked thinking about it or hearing it in the mall, too! It was fun just going to Hot Topic and shopping and you hear this song come on at the mall. This song literally is telling you you'll have a good day. It's nice listening to it especially in the summer. I love this song Panic! At The Disco. Thank you.
